# Modulo inventory

Escopo
- Controle de produtos, categorias e estoque.
- Registro de ledger de movimentos, alertas de minimo e sugestoes simples de compra.

Rotas e entradas
- Stack: `src/modules/inventory/presentation/stacks/inventory.stack.tsx`.
- Base path: `/inventory`.
- Pages:
  - `landing`: `presentation/pages/landing/landing.page`.
  - `home`: `presentation/pages/home/home.page`.
  - `categories`: `presentation/pages/categories/categories.page`.

Modelos principais
- `CategoryModel`: id, name, description, active, createdAt.
- `ProductModel`: id, name, sku, barcode, unit, categoryId, costCents, priceCents, minStock, location, tags, active, stock, createdAt.
- `InventoryMovement`: id, inventoryItemId, direction (in/out), quantity, previousQuantity, nextQuantity, source, reason.
- `InventoryAlertsResponse`: summary + alerts + suggestions.

Services
- `inventory.service.ts`
  - Mock legado (evitar para operacoes reais de estoque).
- `inventory.http.service.ts`
  - Wrapper HTTP (create/list/get/update/delete + movements + alerts).
  - Encapsula `InventoryApi` e converte erros.
- `inventory-api.ts`
  - Endpoints:
  - `/inventory/internal/items`
  - `/inventory/internal/movements`
  - `/inventory/internal/alerts`
  - Usa payloads `CreateInventoryItemPayload` e `CreateInventoryMovementPayload`.

Integracoes
- `schedule` e `work-order` podem referenciar itens de inventory via IDs.

Guardrails
- Operacoes de entrada/saida devem usar `createInventoryMovement()` para manter trilha auditavel.
- Alinhar payload com `CreateInventoryItemPayload` quando integrar com backend.
